idinfo.useconst: This election precinct file should be used as a reference for determining the boundaries of election precincts. The depiction and designation of the election precinct boundaries do not constitute a determination of jurisdictional authority or rights of ownership or entitlement and they are not legal land descriptions. Please consult the appropriate county agency or county election official for additional information regarding election precinct boundaries.

srcinfo.srccontr: Texas Legislative Council and County election officials for all 254 Texas counties. County election officials providing precinct boundary information was collected by the GIS Staff of the Texas Legislative Council and may have been from one or all of the following offices: County Clerk, County Voter Registrar/Tax Assessor-Collector, County Judge, County Elections Administrator.

procstep.procdesc: Precinct boundary data and changes are entered into the Texas Legislative Council's Boundary Definition System (BDS). BDS is an ArcMap10-based GIS application which allows geographical units to be assigned to an area or district using polygons or census block geography. If a precinct boundary does not follow any census geography or polygon boundary, the BDS application also allows for geographic units to be "split" by adding arcs. This enables boundaries that do not follow census geography or are non-visible features to be drawn accurately in the system. After the precinct boundary changes are input by a GIS staff member, a second GIS staff member checks the initial input and makes any corrections as needed. After in-house checking is complete, verification maps of each precinct that changed are printed and then mailed along with a questionnaire to the designated county election official for review. Additional corrections are made, if necessary, based upon responses from the county. When all county verification responses have been received and input as needed, a statewide precinct layer is then created corresponding to that election cycle.
